                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War/1277: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-27">January 27,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received January 27—8:39 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>716. From Pell. At meeting of War Crimes Commission January 25, Norwegian
                    representative reported that his Government would be willing to have all work
                    relating to war crimes centralized in present Commission and that it considered
                    technical committee superfluous. Chinese, Australian, Belgian, Dutch and Polish
                    representatives said the same. Chairman Hurst concurred for Great Britain. No
                    disagreement was expressed. [Pell.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
